theorem interior_eq_closure_iff_clopen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) = closure (A : Set X) ↔ (IsOpen A ∧ IsClosed (A : Set X)) := by
  constructor
  · intro h
    -- First, show `A = interior A`.
    have hA_eq_int : (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) := by
      apply le_antisymm
      ·
        have hA_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure
        simpa [h] using hA_subset
      ·
        exact interior_subset
    -- Hence `A` is open.
    have hOpen : IsOpen A := by
      simpa [hA_eq_int] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)))
    -- Next, show `A = closure A`.
    have hA_eq_cl : (A : Set X) = closure (A : Set X) := by
      calc
        (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) := hA_eq_int
        _ = closure (A : Set X) := h
    -- Hence `A` is closed.
    have hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X) := by
      have h_closed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X)) := isClosed_closure
      simpa [hA_eq_cl] using h_closed_closure
    exact ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩
  · rintro ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩
    have hInt : interior (A : Set X) = A := hOpen.interior_eq
    have hCl  : closure  (A : Set X) = A := hClosed.closure_eq
    simpa [hInt, hCl]

theorem interior_diff_self_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior ((A : Set X) \ A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  simp
